Title: A Classification Problem in the Credit Card Industry: A Comparison of Three Solutions  
Author: Christopher H. Jolly Mukkai S. Krishnamoorthy 
Address: Schenectady, NY 12301, USA  Troy, NY 12180, USA  
Affiliation: GE Corporate Research and Development,  Department of Computer Science, Rensselaer Polytechnic Institute,  
Abstract: Classifying accounts is a critical part of efficiently servicing credit cards. A problem we call the Rule Coverage Problem (RCP) arrises when using rules for specifying a classification strategy, and we develop and compare three approaches for solving this problem. 
