Reference-contexts: An intelligent rule editor should point out each rule covered and the rules covering it. Informally, the Rule Coverage Problem (RCP) is determining if any rules are covered by higher-priority rules. It can be shown that RCP is Co-NP-complete (see <ref> [Garey79] </ref> for an introduction to NP-complete problems). 1.2 Solving RCP We look for potential algorithms for solving RCP by reducing RCP to a better known problems and examining the algorithms developed for them.
